Usage of /usr/bin/trojan-go:
  -add-profile
        Add a new profile with API
  -api string
        Connect to a Trojan-Go API service. "-api add/get/list"
  -api-addr string
        Address of Trojan-Go API service (default "127.0.0.1:10000")
  -cert string
        Certificates of the server (default "server.crt")
  -client
        Run a trojan-go client
  -config string
        Trojan-Go config filename (.yaml/.yml/.json) (default "config.json")
  -delete-profile
        Delete an existing profile with API
  -download-speed-limit int
        Limit the download speed with API
  -ip-limit int
        Limit the number of IP with API
  -key string
        Key of the server (default "server.key")
  -local string
        Local address, e.g. 127.0.0.1:12345
  -modify-profile
        Modify an existing profile with API
  -password string
        Password for authentication
  -remote string
        Remote address, e.g. 127.0.0.1:12345
  -server
        Run a trojan-go server
  -stdin-format string
        Read from standard input (yaml/json) (default "disabled")
  -stdin-suppress-hint
        Suppress hint text
  -target-hash string
        Hash of the target user
  -target-password string
        Password of the target user
  -upload-speed-limit int
        Limit the upload speed with API
  -url string
        Setup trojan-go client with a url link
  -url-option string
        URL mode options (default "mux=true;listen=127.0.0.1:1080")
  -version
        Display version and help info